    "description": "Ecuador is a relatively small territory characterized by 4 distinct natural regions where culture and bio-diversity alike have flourished pristine and unique; modern infraestructure, various UNESCO Heritage Sites, cultural splendor, wildlife watching, sublime scenery, snow-capped highlands and volcanoes, waves splashing white-sand beaches and more! wrapped-up in an easy-access compact territory the size of Nevada; through this all-inclusive package, enjoy the 4 natural regions of Ecuador to its fullest. The COAST region, the fertile and ever labored lands stretching to the west of the Andean range, splashed by the ever-giving Pacific Ocean. The ANDES region, consisting of the Andean and inter-andean highlands, containing volcanoes, snow-capped peaks and culturally rich cities. The AMAZONIA basin and Amazon jungle rainforest, graced by huge national parks and Amerindian untouchable zones, where free men still roam and live traditionally. The GALAPAGOS archipelago region comprising the Galápagos Islands, some 1,000 kilometers (620 mi) west of the mainland in the Pacific Ocean; in itself a National Park, UNESCO World Heritage Site and jealously guarded Marine Reserve comprising 133,000 kilometers (51,352 square mi).",
